      .one-col
        %h3 Hello! My name is Stuart. I have a mixed background in design and development.
        %p From an early age, I was always creating art. I began coding in middle school back in the 90s. I got into making websites and even into 3d animation.
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{:role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/stuart-draws.jpg"})"}
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{:role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/stuart-codes.jpg"})"}
      .one-col
        %h3 I ended up doing a double major in Art &amp; Design and Computer Science.
        %p Then I got my Master's in a combo of those two disciplines called Visualization Science.
      .one-col
        %h3 I've gone from creating visual effects for film to developing digital products on the mobile and web.
        %p
          I loved using my visual creativity to craft fire on films like
          %span.italic How To Train Your Dragon
      .one-col
      .one-col.col3
        %h3 Since then, I've been working at early-stage startups working on mobile and web products.
        %p I've had the opportunity to wear many hats on these small teams. I've found that my strengths are around:
      .grid-span.two-col
        %ul.dark-list
          %li.one
            Building a great experience for people using digital interfaces.
        %ul.dark-list
          %li.two
            Matching the user's needs with business needs to create lasting growth.
        %ul.dark-list
          %li.three
            Crafting interfaces that are functional and aesthetically pleasing.
